Disentangle the SRV by PCD. In Step 3, we conduct PCD to disentangle the SRV into PCs ranked according to the descending order of their eigenvalues. In PCD, PCs are a sets k PCs, denoted as PC = {PC1, PC2, …PCk}, where PCn is a set of projections of the a-vectors from SRV on it and denoted as PCn={\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
